Amanda Khoza, News24iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; A KwaZulu-Natal private security company on Sunday issued a warning to motorists to be vigilant after a Durban North man was abducted in a foiled hijacking on Saturday night.Blue Security operations manager Brian Jackson said the suspects hijacked the man on Fairway Road at around 22:44 and then crashed his vehicle on the M4.&nbsp; In a Facebook message on Sunday morning Jackson said: &ldquo;Four armed men hijacked him [the motorist] of his vehicle and pushed him into the back seat. They drove onto the M4 towards the CBD but they lost control of the vehicle and crashed into a barrier.&rdquo;The men then fled the scene, leaving the uninjured motorist in the vehicle.Jackson urged motorists to be vigilant when driving home from work, especially at night.&ldquo;Driveways are prime spots for hijackings. It&rsquo;s important to always check your surroundings for any suspicious individuals or vehicles that could be lurking nearby.&ldquo;If you notice anything that makes you feel uncomfortable, rather drive around the block before pulling into the driveway.&rdquo;Jackson said people should call the police to investigate if they feel unsafe.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.